*colo-1.13 (03 Sep 2004)

  03 Sep 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> -files/colo-1.4-gentoo.patch,
  -files/colo-1.6-gentoo.patch, -files/default.boot.example,
  +files/default.colo, +files/menu-linux.colo, -colo-1.10.ebuild,
  colo-1.11.ebuild, +colo-1.13.ebuild, -colo-1.4.ebuild, -colo-1.6.ebuild,
  -colo-1.8.ebuild, -colo-1.9.ebuild:
  New colo revision, cleaned up older revisions, Marked 1.11 stable.

*colo-1.11 (02 Aug 2004)

  02 Aug 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org>
  +files/colo-linker-overlap-fix.patch, colo-1.10.ebuild, +colo-1.11.ebuild,
  colo-1.9.ebuild:
  Revision bump to 1.11, and 1.9/1.10 bumped to stable.

  28 Jun 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> colo-1.4.ebuild,
  colo-1.6.ebuild, colo-1.8.ebuild:
  Marked stable on mips.

*colo-1.10 (25 Jun 2004)

  25 Jun 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> :
  Long-overdue revision bump. There may be issues in building w/ gcc-3.4.x, but
  these will get ironed out later.

*colo-1.9 (15 May 2004)

  15 May 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> +colo-1.9.ebuild:
  Long overdue version bump...

*colo-1.8 (29 Apr 2004)

  29 Apr 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> +colo-1.8.ebuild:
  New revision which adds tftp/dhcp support for netbooting.

*colo-1.6 (21 Apr 2004)

  21 Apr 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> +files/colo-1.6-gentoo.patch,
  +colo-1.6.ebuild:
  New revision of colo. Adds a number of new features, including booting from
  RAID, loadable initrd, and other bits.

*colo-1.4 (05 Apr 2004)

  05 Apr 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> colo-1.4.ebuild,
  files/colo-1.4-gentoo.patch files/default.boot.example:
  Initial import of a modern bootloader for Cobalt MIPS systems

